00:01:00.993 --> 00:01:02.462
here it is.

00:01:02.495 --> 00:01:04.464
So it's been around for
a couple thousand years,

00:01:04.497 --> 00:01:06.732
and it's basically people, they
kidnap falcons out of the wild,

00:01:06.765 --> 00:01:09.936
and then they train them to
hunt for them.

00:01:09.969 --> 00:01:12.472
Now, the popularity fizzled out

00:01:12.505 --> 00:01:15.408
with the invention
of the supermarket.

00:01:15.441 --> 00:01:17.076
People were like, "Hey man,
I don't know if we need

00:01:17.109 --> 00:01:18.744
a bird of prey to bring us
our super anymore."

00:01:18.777 --> 00:01:20.780
We can just go to the meat
aisle at the grocery store."

00:01:20.813 --> 00:01:24.317
But a group of lunatics kept
this tradition alive,

00:01:24.350 --> 00:01:26.319
and my father was one of them.

00:01:26.352 --> 00:01:29.622
Now here's the thing: You can
legally do falconry,

00:01:29.655 --> 00:01:30.990
but you need a license.

00:01:31.023 --> 00:01:32.959
And in order to get a license,

00:01:32.992 --> 00:01:34.594
you got to jump through
a few hoops.

00:01:34.627 --> 00:01:37.897
Number one, you have got to do
a two-year apprenticeship

00:01:37.930 --> 00:01:39.732
with a master falconer.

00:01:39.765 --> 00:01:43.669
Now, of all the people that
I could spend two years with,

00:01:43.702 --> 00:01:47.607
I think master falconer is
probably at the bottom of that.

00:01:47.640 --> 00:01:50.576
After that, you have to build
an enclosure for this falcon

00:01:50.609 --> 00:01:51.978
to live in.

00:01:52.011 --> 00:01:53.779
Then you need to take
a written test.

00:01:53.812 --> 00:01:55.448
Well, my dad's like, fuck that.
Okay?

00:01:55.481 --> 00:01:57.617
I'm not gonna let
the government tell me

00:01:57.650 --> 00:01:59.485
what I can and can't do.

00:01:59.518 --> 00:02:02.121
And so he gets a book
on falconry

00:02:02.154 --> 00:02:04.190
and he reads about
three chapters into it,

00:02:04.223 --> 00:02:07.460
and then he comes home
with a baby falcon.

00:02:10.829 --> 00:02:12.532
To this day, I have no idea

00:02:12.565 --> 00:02:14.800
where he actually got this
falcon from.

00:02:14.833 --> 00:02:19.805
He claims he found it while he
was hiking through the woods.

00:02:19.838 --> 00:02:22.675
Now, I've done a lot of hiking
in the woods,

00:02:22.708 --> 00:02:26.012
and I have never seen a baby
falcon just laying there

00:02:26.045 --> 00:02:28.114
looking for a good home.

00:02:28.147 --> 00:02:30.316
And it seemed like
an odd coincidence

00:02:30.349 --> 00:02:33.119
that he just happened to be
reading a book on falconry

00:02:33.152 --> 00:02:34.787
and he finds a falcon.

00:02:34.820 --> 00:02:36.289
Either way, he brings it home.

00:02:36.322 --> 00:02:37.390
But he doesn't have
an enclosure.

00:02:37.423 --> 00:02:38.958
He didn't build an enclosure.

00:02:38.991 --> 00:02:40.793
So here's what he does.

00:02:40.826 --> 00:02:43.896
He reassembles an old dog crate
we have in our living room,

00:02:43.929 --> 00:02:45.998
and he throws it in there.

00:02:46.031 --> 00:02:48.467
Now, I have to admit, as a kid,
we have a pet falcon,

00:02:48.500 --> 00:02:49.669
it's kind of cool, all right.

00:02:49.702 --> 00:02:50.836
I had a friend come over,

00:02:50.869 --> 00:02:52.338
he's like, "Hey, I just got
a new dog."

00:02:52.371 --> 00:02:53.706
And I was like,
"I see your dog,

00:02:53.739 --> 00:02:57.343
and I raise you a fucking
falcon, my friend.

00:02:57.376 --> 00:03:00.046
Get that dog shit out of here."

00:03:00.079 --> 00:03:01.347
But then something happens.

00:03:01.380 --> 00:03:02.682
About six, seven months goes
by,

00:03:02.715 --> 00:03:05.484
and this thing grows up,
and it is now

00:03:05.517 --> 00:03:07.320
a full blown bird of prey.

00:03:07.353 --> 00:03:09.922
And I'll tell you this: It does
not want to go back

00:03:09.955 --> 00:03:11.924
in the dog crate anymore.

00:03:11.957 --> 00:03:13.659
So here's what my dad does.

00:03:13.692 --> 00:03:17.530
He lets it fly around
our house,

00:03:17.563 --> 00:03:20.700
so right off the bat we let
our cats out one day

00:03:20.733 --> 00:03:22.168
and they're like,
"We're out of here.

00:03:22.201 --> 00:03:23.869
Like, fuck you guys,
we're out."

00:03:23.902 --> 00:03:26.539
One of 'em I think had, like,
a stick with a handkerchief

00:03:26.572 --> 00:03:28.774
with his shit filled on it
hobo style and just...

00:03:28.807 --> 00:03:32.445
Our dog all day long just hides
under the desk, okay?

00:03:32.478 --> 00:03:36.215
He's traumatized.
He's got PTSD.

00:03:36.248 --> 00:03:37.917
But here's the worst part.

00:03:37.950 --> 00:03:41.754
So this falcon loved to perch
itself on our refrigerator,

00:03:41.787 --> 00:03:43.389
right on the freezer door,

00:03:43.422 --> 00:03:47.059
so literally every time I went
to go get a Klondike bar,

00:03:47.092 --> 00:03:52.198
I had to ask myself, what would
you do for this Klondike bar?

00:03:52.231 --> 00:03:55.067
Like, is it worth getting
a talon in your nut sack

00:03:55.100 --> 00:03:59.071
for that delicious
vanilla ice cream,

00:03:59.104 --> 00:04:02.275
chocolate covered goodness?

00:04:02.308 --> 00:04:03.709
One of the scariest things is,

00:04:03.742 --> 00:04:05.645
when you would open
the freezer door,

00:04:05.678 --> 00:04:08.881
it would just swing open with
it and then just swing close.

00:04:08.914 --> 00:04:11.717
No change of expression on its
face whatsoever.

00:04:11.750 --> 00:04:14.620
I don't know if it was thinking
of unicorns and rainbows,

00:04:14.653 --> 00:04:19.158
or thinking about mass murder
of my whole family.

00:04:19.191 --> 00:04:21.794
Now, once a day, my dad has
to take this thing outside

00:04:21.827 --> 00:04:24.764
in our backyard, but falcons
don't want to live

00:04:24.797 --> 00:04:27.166
in captivity, so here's what
you have to do

00:04:27.199 --> 00:04:28.934
to keep them from flying away.

00:04:28.967 --> 00:04:32.338
You have to tie a string to
their leg, give it some slack,

00:04:32.371 --> 00:04:35.675
and then hold on to
the other end.

00:04:35.708 --> 00:04:37.243
By the way, my dad had
none of the falcon gear

00:04:37.276 --> 00:04:38.844
that was necessary.

00:04:38.877 --> 00:04:40.980
Like, you're supposed to have
a thick leather glove;

00:04:41.013 --> 00:04:42.114
he had an old oven mitt.

00:04:42.147 --> 00:04:43.816
That's what he would carry--

00:04:43.849 --> 00:04:46.952
that's what he would carry it
out into the backyard with.

00:04:46.985 --> 00:04:49.622
So we'd hold the other end,
and he would let it go.

00:04:49.655 --> 00:04:53.125
And so it was basically like he
was flying a falcon kite

00:04:53.158 --> 00:04:56.262
in our backyard.

00:04:56.295 --> 00:04:58.464
And it probably wouldn't have
been a big deal,

00:04:58.497 --> 00:05:03.803
but at the time,
we lived in a motel.

00:05:03.836 --> 00:05:05.304
Yeah.

00:05:05.337 --> 00:05:06.939
So my parents thought it would
be a good idea

00:05:06.972 --> 00:05:09.141
to buy a motel and then we
would live in an apartment

00:05:09.174 --> 00:05:10.643
attached to it.

00:05:10.676 --> 00:05:12.945
